            <div1 id="BQ-11-1-0012">
                <pb id="p11-62" n="62"/>
                <div2>
                    <head>
                        <title type="main">
                            <hi rend="b">Blake in the News</hi>
                        </title>
                    </head>
                    <p>“Eight years ago a girl of 20 [Margaret Trudeau] met a prime
                        minister of 49 [Pierre Trudeau, Prime Minister of Canada] on the island of
                        Tahiti. They shared a passion for William Blake, the poet who once wrote,
                        ‘Love to faults is always blind / Always is to joy
                        inclin’d.’” Quoted from Ellen Goodman in her
                        syndicated newspaper column <hi rend="i">At Large</hi>, for Thursday, 31
                        March 1977.</p>
                    <p>On 28 April CBS-TV aired “Tiger, Tiger,” a documentary on
                        the Bengal tiger, an endangered species.</p>
                </div2>
            </div1>
